    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-08-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="576"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Newport, R. I.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-08-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 9th instant, relative to the surrender of Mataafa and his
                    chiefs, and inquiring what action on the part of the three treaty powers is
                    demanded by the present situation at Samoa, and what disposition in the opinion
                    of Her Majesty’s Government should be made of Mataafa.</p>
                <p>I have communicated to my Government by telegraph the substance of your note,
                    copy of which I am sending by today’s mail.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
